William Miranda Marín, the former mayor of Caguas, Puerto Rico, has passed away. President Obama released a statement expressing his sadness and highlighting Miranda Marín's dedication to public service and economic development. Miranda Marín was admired for his commitment to the people he represented and his efforts to promote citizen participation in government. The President and First Lady Michelle Obama recalled their warm reception by Miranda Marín during a visit to Puerto Rico, where he showed them the Botanical Gardens of Caguas. His legacy lives on through those he empowered to continue working towards expanding opportunities for Puerto Ricans and Americans. The President extended his condolences to Miranda Marín's family.